    "His nephew, John Willis Clark, took over his uncle's notes, devoting more than a decade to turn them into the four-volume <em>The Architectural History of the University of Cambridge, and of the Colleges of Cambridge and Eton</em> which appeared in 1886.": [],
    "Willis founded the architectural monograph, the \"biography of a building,\" which remains one of the most flourishing categories of medieval architecture (Crossley).": [
